### 2. Adding "Analysis" for the Next Agents

It is highly recommended to **not** add generative analysis to this specific script.

The Hugging Face models currently running in your cascade (`distilbert`, `deberta`, `bart-large-mnli`) are strictly **Zero-Shot Classifiers**. They are incredibly efficient at looking at a piece of text and sorting it into predefined buckets (Feature, Complaint, Trend, Insight). However, they are fundamentally incapable of generating new text.

To extract deeper, meeting-level analysis—such as the 2-line summary, Major Decisions, Problem/Solution mapping, and Tone—you need a generative LLM. Attempting to force Agent 1 to do this would require hooking up the Gemini API here, which would slow down your ingestion pipeline and mix your structural data extraction (Layer 2) with your generative insights (Layer 1).

Keep Agent 1 exactly as it is: a fast, unbreakable, structural parser that produces clean JSON fragments. Pass this clean JSON to **Agent 2**, and let Agent 2 use Gemini to read the fragments and write the comprehensive analytical summaries.

